NAME - ::<namespace>:: emulation_cfm_mip_mep_config

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

This procedure configures the Maintenance Point properties. This protocol is available only when using IxTclNetwork. The GUI equivalent is in the section Protocols/Carrier Ethernet where CFM/Y.1731/PBB-TE is enabled.

SYNOPSIS - ::<namespace>::emulation_cfm_mip_mep_config

List arguments in the alphabetical order or in the reverse alphabetical order.

ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

-bridge_handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The value of the -bridge_handle parameter must be a bridge handle returned by ::::emulation_cfm_config procedure. Maintenance Point properties will be asociated with the CFM Bridge specified with this parameter.Mandatory when -mode is add.This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxN.

DEFAULT

 None

-mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

Action to perform. This parameter is supported using the following

Valid options are:

create

Create new Maintenance Points on -port_handle.

modify

Modify Maintenance Point specified with -handle parameter.

enable

Enable Maintenance Points specified with -handle parameter.

disable

Disable Maintenance Points specified with -handle parameter.

remove

Remove Maintenance Points specified with -handle parameter.

DEFAULT

 None

-md_meg_handle_distribution

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxN.

Valid options are:

round_robin

Distribute the MD handles in a round robin manner.

repeat_count

Use next MD handle every time -md_meg_handle_repeat_count expires.

DEFAULT

round_robin

-md_meg_handle_list

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

List of handles from ::::emulation_cfm_md_meg_config. These handles will be associated with MPs in the manner specified with -md_meg_handle_distribution and -md_meg_handle_repeat_count. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxN.When mode is -modify this parameter must have only one md_meg handle. The md_meg handle associated with the mip_mep handle specified with -handle parameter will be changed with the md_meg handle from -md_meg_handle_list parameter.

DEFAULT

 None

-md_meg_handle_repeat_count

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

How many MPs to configure with the same MP Name before using the next MD handle from the list. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxN. This parameter is used only when -mode is create.

DEFAULT

1

-meg_id_format

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The MEG identifier format. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxN. Valid when allow_cfm_maid_formats is 1.icc_based_format - Use next MD handle every time -md_meg_handle_repeat_count expires. primary_vid - a number from 0 to 4095. char_string - a valid string. 2_octet_integer - a number from 0 to 65535. rfc_2685_vpn_id - must be formatted - where is from 0 to 16777215 and is from 0 to 4292967295.

DEFAULT

icc_based_format
